[The most interesting aspects of this survey are the conclusions
that: (1) Even in a highly vaccinated population, susceptible
individuals remain due to primary and secondary vaccination failure;
(2) the geographical clustering of 2-dose vaccinated patients may
indicate cold chain problems in the past; and (3) that the outbreak
was maintained by separate introductions of D6 genotype measles virus
from neighboring Ukraine. - Mod.CP]
